The paper deals with data structures and algorithms for problems on unit discs and arcs of their boundary in the plane, which is a classic topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper presents dynamic data structures for maintaining the union of unit discs under insertions, which involves maintaining lower envelopes of pseudo-lines, a well-studied problem in data structures (cs.DS). The paper also presents a dynamic range searching structure for circular arcs, which is a problem in computational geometry and numerical analysis (cs.CG, cs.NA). The paper's focus on efficiency and near-optimal overhead suggests that it may also be relevant to the field of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and control systems (cs.SY).
